text: Camden County is a county located in the southeastern corner of the U.S. state of Georgia. According to the 2020 Census, the population was 54,768. Its county seat is Woodbine, and the largest city is St. Marys. It is one of the first counties of Georgia, created February 5, 1777. ==References== ==Other websites== *Camden County website *Camden County Schools, Board of Education *Democratic Party, Camden County, Georgia *"Camden County" New Georgia Encyclopedia *Camden County historical marker Category:1777 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state)
